title: Daniel Sahuleka - The Universal Masters Collection (2003)
description:
DaniÃƒÂ«l Sahuleka (born 6 December 1950 in Semarang, Indonesia) is a Dutch musician and singer of South Moluccan and Sundanese-Chinese descent.

Sahuleka created a portfolio of 110 compositions, and many of his songs are well known such as "You Make My World So Colourful" from the album Daniel Sahuleka (1977), and "Don't Sleep Away the Night" (1980). In the early 1980s, he had hits with "Wake Up" and "We'll Go Out Tonight".

In Indonesia, Los Angeles and Europe, Sahuleka has received several prestigious awards.
